Task:
Assemble a final, polished research report from the chapter drafts above.

Required structure:
- `# Title` (concise, descriptive title for the report)
- `## Executive Answer` (direct answer to the research question in 2-4 sentences)
- `## Key Findings` (bulleted list of the most important facts across all chapters)
- One `## Section` per chapter, incorporating the chapter content with editorial polish
- `## Limitations And Open Gaps` (combined from all chapters plus any cross-cutting issues)

Style rules:
- Write smooth transitions between chapters.
- Prefer short paragraphs and direct wording.
- Synthesize across chapters; do not merely concatenate them.
- If evidence is thin or incomplete, say so plainly.
- Do not fabricate inline citations or source names beyond what appears in the chapter drafts.
- The runtime will append the final referenced-sources section separately.
- Adapt the report length to the content available: roughly 400-800 words for a 2-chapter report, 800-1500 words for 4-5 chapters.
- Return Markdown only.